 was that of [[Madeline & Louise|Madeline Lynn]] in ''[[Gilmore Girls]]'', which she played from 2000 to 2004.<ref>{{cite web|author=Emily Yahr |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/arts-and-entertainment/wp/2014/10/01/gilmore-girls-on-netflix-a-refresher-and-ranking-on-each-season/ |title='Gilmore Girls' on Netflix: A refresher (and ranking) on each season |publisher=The Washington Post |date=31 January 2016 |accessdate=13 April 2020}}</ref> \n\nCole's final acting credit was in 2011. She has since worked as an acting coach in [[Denver, Colorado]].<ref>{{cite web|author= |url=https://peakactingstudios.com/about-us/276-shelly-cole.html |title=Shelly Cole |publisher=Peak Acting Studios |date= |accessdate=13 April 2020}}</ref> In 2018, she directed an independent film entitled ''Body Keepers''. \n\n== Filmography ==\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n|2000\n|''{{sortname|The|Theory of Everything|nolink=1}}''\n|Janice\n|TV movie\n|-\n|2000\n|''{{sortname|The|Princess & the Barrio Boy|nolink=1}}''\n|Homeless Girl\n|TV movie\n|-\n|2000\u20132004\n|''[[Gilmore Girls]]''\n|[[List of Gilmore Girls characters#Chilton|Madeline Lynn]]\n|33 episodes\n|-\n|2000\u20132001\n|''[[Boston Public]]''\n|Susan\n|Episodes: \"[[List of Boston Public episodes#Season 1 .282000.E2.80.932001.29|Chapter Six]]\" & \"[[List of Boston Public episodes#Season 2 .282001.E2.80.932002.29|Chapter Twenty-Nine]]\"\n|-\n|2001\n|''{{sortname|The|Guardian|The Guardian (TV series)}}''\n|April Evans\n|Episode: \"Lolita?\"\n|-\n|2001\n|''[[ER (TV series)|ER]]''\n|Laura Avery\n|Episode: \"[[ER (season 8)#Episodes|Supplies and Demands]]\"\n|-\n|2002\n|''[[NYPD Blue]]''\n|Baby Doll\n|Episode: \"Safari, So Good\"\n|-\n|2002\n|''BraceFace Brandi''\n|Christina\n|Short film\n|-\n|2003\n|''[[Prey for Rock & Roll]]''\n|Sally\n|\n|-\n|2003\n|''{{sortname|8|Simple Rules}}''\n|Christina\n|Episode: \"[[8 Simple Rules (season 1)#Episodes|Kerry's Big Advent