ilm)|The Tales of Hoffmann]]'' || data-sort-value=\"Powell\"| [[Michael Powell]], [[Emeric Pressburger]] || United Kingdom\n|-\n| colspan=2| ''[[Umberto D.]]'' (1952) || data-sort-value=\"De Sica\"| [[Vittorio De Sica]] || Italy\n|-\n| ''[[Walking the Streets of Moscow]]'' (1963) || ''Ya shagayu po Moskve'' || data-sort-value=\"Daneliya\"| [[Georgiy Daneliya]] || Soviet Union\n|-\n| data-sort-value=\"Warrior\"| ''[[The Warrior (1916 film)|The Warrior]]'' || ''Maciste alpino'' || data-sort-value=\"Maggi\"| [[Luigi Maggi]], [[Luigi Romano Borgnetto]] || Italy\n|-\n| ''[[Without Pity]]'' || ''Senza piet\u00e0'' || data-sort-value=\"Lattuada\"| [[Alberto Lattuada]] || Italy\n|}\n{| class=\"sortable wikitable\" style=\"width:95%; margin-top:2px; margin-bottom:0px\"\n! colspan=4| Documentaries on Cinema\n|-\n!| English title\n! Original title\n! Director(s)\n! Production country\n|-style=\"background:#FFDEAD\"\n| {{N/A}} || ''Animata resistenza'' || Francesco Montagner & Alberto Girotto || Italy\n|-\n|''Flowers of Taipei \u2013 Taiwan New Cinema'' || ''Guangyin de gushi \u2013 Taiwan Xin Dianying'' || Chinlin Hsieh || Taiwan\n|-\n| ''Red Chairs - Parma and the Cinema'' || ''Poltrone Rosse - Parma e il Cinema'' || [[Francesco Barilli]] || Italy\n|-\n| colspan=4| Note: incomplete list\n|}\n:<span style=\"background:#FFDEAD\">Highlighted titles</span> indicate the Best Restored Film and Best Documentary on Cinema official awards respectively.\n\n===Biennale College - Cinema===\nThe following films were screened for the \"Biennale College - Cinema\" section, a higher education training workshop for micro-budget feature films:<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.labiennale.org/en/cinema/71st-festival/line-up/off-sel/bcc |title=Biennale College - Cinema |work=labiennale.org |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140929220220/http://www.labiennale.org/en/cinema/71st-festival/line-up/off-sel/bcc |archivedate=29 September 2014 |access-date=13 April 2018  }}</ref>\n{