 Best Actress]]: [[Alba Rohrwacher]] for ''[[Hungry Hearts (2014 film)|Hungry Hearts]]''\n*[[Marcello Mastroianni Award]]: Romain Paul for his role in ''[[The Last Hammer Blow]]''\n* Best Screenplay Award: [[Rakhshan Banietemad]] & [[Farid Mostafavi]] for  ''[[Tales (film)|Tales]]''\n*[[Special Jury Prize (Venice Film Festival)|Special Jury Prize]]: ''[[Sivas (film)|Sivas]]'' by [[Kaan Mujdeci]]\n\n'''Horizons (Orizzonti)''' \n*Best Film: ''[[Court (film)|Court]]'' by [[Chaitanya Tamhane]]\n*Best Director: ''[[Theeb]]'' by [[Naji Abu Nowar]]\n*Special Jury Prize: ''[[Belluscone, una storia siciliana]]'' by [[Franco Maresco]]\n*Special Award for Best Actor or Actress: [[Emir Had\u017eihafizbegovi\u0107]] for ''[[These Are the Rules]]''\n*Horizons Award for Best Short Film: ''[[Maryam (2014 film)|Maryam]]'' by [[Sidi Saleh]]\n\n'''Lion of the Future'''\n:Luigi De Laurentiis Award for a Debut Film: ''[[Court (film)|Court]]'' by [[Chaitanya Tamhane]] (Horizons)\n\n'''Venice Classics Awards'''\n*Best Restored Film: ''[[A Special Day]]'' (''Una giornata particolare'') by [[Ettore Scola]]\n*Best Documentary on Cinema: ''Animata Resistenza'' by Francesco Montagner and Alberto Girotto\n\n'''Special Awards'''\n*[[Golden Lion#Golden Lion Honorary Award|Golden Lion for Lifetime Achievement]]: [[Thelma Schoonmaker]] and [[Frederick Wiseman]]\n*Persol Tribute to Visionary Talent Award: [[Frances McDormand]]<ref name=\"McDormand\">{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/entertainment-arts-29027512 |title=Frances McDormand honoured at Venice Film Festival |accessdate=3 September 2014 |work=BBC News}}</ref>\n*Jaeger-LeCoultre Glory to the Filmmaker Award: [[James Franco]];<ref>http://www.cineblog.it/post/430298/venezia-2014-premio-premio-jaeger-lecoultre-per-james-franco</ref>\n*L\u2019Or\u00e9al Paris per il Cinema Award: Valentina Corti\n\n===Autonomous sections===\nThe following official and collateral awards were conferred to films of the autonomous sections:<ref name=\"collateral-71\" />\n\n'''29th Venice International Critics' Week'''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cinecriticaweb.it/panoramiche/no-ones-child-di-%E2%80%8Bvuk-rsumovic-vince-la-29-settimana-internazionale-della-critica-premio-del-pubblico-rarovideo |accessdate=6 September 2014 |title=NO ONE\u2019S CHILD di Vuk R\u0161umovi\u0107 vince la 29. Settimana Internazionale della Critica (Premio del Pubblico RaroVideo) |language=Italian}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.sicvenezia.it/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/ENG_winner.doc |title=RaroVideo Audience Award to No One's Child by Vuk R\u0161umovi\u0107 |accessdate=7 September 2014 |work=SNCCI |language=Italian}}</ref> \n* RaroVideo Audience Award for Best Film: ''[[No One's Child]]'' by Vuk R\u0161umovi\u0107\n* FEDEORA (Federation of Film Critics of Europe and the Mediterranean) Best Screenplay: ''No One's Child'' by Vuk R\u0161umovi\u0107\n* FEDEORA Best Film: ''[[Flapping in The Middle of Nowhere]]'' by Nguy\u1ec5n Ho\u00e0ng \u0110i\u1ec7p\n* [[FIPRESCI|FIPRESCI Awards]] - Best Film (Critics' Week): ''No One's Child'' (''Nicije dete'') by Vuk R\u0161umovi\u0107<ref name=\"fipresci\" />\n* \"Civitas Vitae prossima\" Award: Ivan Gergolet (director) for ''[[Dancing with Maria]]''\n\n'''Venice Days (Giornate degli Autori)'''<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.venice-days.com/NEWS.asp?id=1&id_dettaglio=494&t=Collateral%20awards&lang=eng |title=Collateral awards |work=venice-days.com |accessdate=3 May 2018}}</ref>     \n* Venice Days Award: ''[[Return to Ithaca]]'' by [[Laurent Cantet]]<ref name=\"VeniceDays\">{{cite web |url=http://www.venice-days.com/NEWS.asp?id=1&id_dettaglio=489&t=%3Ci%3ERetour%20a%20Ithaque%3C/i%3E%20wins%20the%20Venice%20Days%20Award&lang=eng |title=Retour a Ithaque wins the Venice Days Award |work=venice-days.com |accessdate=3 May 2018}}</ref>\n* BNL People's Choice Award: ''[[The Farewell Party]]'' by  Tal Granit and Sharon Maymon<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.venice-days.com/NEWS.asp?id=1&id_dettaglio=495&t=BNL%20People%27s%3Cbr%3EChoice%20Award%3Cbr%3Egoes%20to%20%3Ci%3EThe%20Farewell%20Party%3C/i%3E&lang=eng |title=BNL People's Choice Award goes to The Farewell Party |work=venice-days.com |accessdate=3 May 2018}}</ref>\n* Europa Cinemas Label Award for Best European Film: ''[[The Dinner (2014 film)|The Dinner]]'' by  [[Ivano De Matteo]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.venice-days.com/NEWS.asp?id=1&id_dettaglio=493&t=%3Ci%3EThe%20Dinner%3C/i%3E%20wins%20Europa%20Cinemas%20Label&lang=eng |title=The Dinner wins Europa Cinemas Label |work=venice-days.com |accessdate=3 May 2018}}</ref>\n* Fedeora Awards:\n**Best Film: ''[[One on One (2014 film)|One on One]]'' by [[Kim Ki-duk]]\n**Best director of a debut film: [[Aditya Vikram Sengupta]] for ''[[Asha Jaoar Majhe|Labour of Love]]''\n* Brian Award - UAAR: ''The Farewell Party'' (''Mita Tova'') by Tal Granit and Sharon Maymon\n* Queer Lion Award 2014: ''Summer Nights'' (''Les nuits d\u2019\u00e9t\u00e9') by Mario Fanfani\n* Gillo Pontecorvo Arcobaleno Latino Award: ''The Show MAS Go On'' by R\u00e4 di Martino\n* Cinecibo Award: ''The Dinner'' by  Ivano De Matteo\n* Pasinetti Special Award: ''The Dinner'' by Ivano De Matteo\n* Open Award: R\u00e4 di Martino for ''The Show MAS Go On''\n* Akai International Film Festival Prize for Best Actor: Jacopo Olmo Antinori for ''The Dinner''<ref name=Akai />\n\n===Other collateral awards===\nThe following collateral awards were conferred to films of the official selection:<ref name=\"collateral-71\">{{cite web|url=http://www.labiennale.org/en/cinema/news/06-09c.html?back=true |title=Collateral Awards of the 71st Venice Film Festival |work=labiennale.org |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141007075607/http://www.labiennale.org/en/cinema/news/06-09c.html?back=true |archivedate=7 October 2014 }}</ref>\n* [[FIPRESCI|FIPRESCI Awards]] - Best Film (Main competition): ''[[The Look of Silence]]'' by [[Joshua Oppenheimer]]<ref name=\"fipresci\">{{cite web|url=http://www.fipresci.org/awards/2014 |title=FIPRESCI Awards 2014 |work=fipresci.org |accessdate=3 May 2018}}</ref>\n* [[SIGNIS|SIGNIS Award]]: ''[[Far from Men]]'' (''Loin des hommes'') by [[David Oelhoffen]]\n::Special mention ''[[99 Homes]]'' by [[Ramin Bahrani]]\n* Francesco Pasinetti (SNGCI) Award:\n**Best Film: ''[[Black Souls]]'' (''Anime nere'') by  [[Francesco Munzi]]\n**Best Actor: [[Elio Germano]] for ''[[Leopardi (film)|Leopardi]]'' \n**Best Actress: [[Alba Rohrwacher]] for ''[[Hungry Hearts (2014 film)|Hungry Hearts]]''\n**Special Award: [[Saverio Costanzo]] (director) for ''Hungry Hearts''\n**Special Award: [[Pierfrancesco Favino]] (actor) for ''[[Without Pity (2014 film)|Without Pity]]'' (Horizons)\n* Leoncino d'Oro Agiscuola Award: ''[[Birdman (film)|Birdman]]'' by [[Alejandro Gonz\u00e1lez I\u00f1\u00e1rritu|Alej\u00e1ndro G. I\u00f1\u00e1rritu]]\n::Cinema for UNICEF mention: ''Hungry Hearts'' by Saverio Costanzo\n* Arca CinemaGiovani Award:\n**Best Film of Venezia 71: ''Far from Men'' by David Oelhoffen\n**Best Italian film: ''[[Belluscone: A Sicilian Story]]'' (''Belluscone. Una storia siciliana'') by [[Franco Maresco]] (Horizons)\n* CICAE - Cinema d\u2019Arte e d\u2019Essai Award: ''[[Heaven Knows What]]'' by [[Safdie brothers|Josh and Ben Safdie]] (Horizons)\n* Fedeora Award for Best Euro-Mediterranean film: ''The Look of Silence'' by Joshua Oppenheimer\n* FEDIC Award: ''On the Bride's Side'' (''Io sto con la sposa'') by Antonio Augugliaro, Gabriele Del Grande, Khaled Soliman Al Nassiry (Horizons)\n::Special mention: ''[[Italy in a Day]]'' by [[Gabriele Salvatores]]\n* Fondazione Mimmo Rotella Award: Luigi Musini (producer) for ''Black Souls''\n* Future Film Festival Digital Award: ''Birdman'' by Alejandro Gonz\u00e1lez I\u00f1\u00e1rritu\n::Special mention: ''Italy in a day'' by Gabriele Salvatores\n* P. Nazareno Taddei Award: ''Birdman'' by Alejandro Gonz\u00e1lez I\u00f1\u00e1rritu\n* Lanterna Magica (CGS) Award: ''[[The Last Hammer Blow]]'' (''Le dernier coup de marteau'') by [[Alix Delaporte]]\n* Golden Mouse: ''The Look of Silence'' by Joshua Oppenheimer\n* Silver Mouse: ''[[Olive Kitteridge (miniseries)|Olive Kitteridge]]'' by [[Lisa Cholodenko]] (Out of competition)\n* The Most Innovative Budget: ''Italy in a Day'' by Gabriele Salvatores\n* Interfilm Award for Promoting Interreligious Dialogue: ''Far from Men'' by David Oelhoffen\n* Young Jury Members of the Vittorio Veneto Film Festival:\n**Best film: ''99 Homes'' by Ramin Bahrani\n**Best actor: [[Elio Germano]] (actor) for ''Leopardi''\n::Special mention: [[Fatih Akin]] (director) for ''[[The Cut (2014 film)|The Cut]]''\n* Green Drop Award: ''[[The Postman's White Nights]]'' (''Belye nochi pochtalona Alekseya Tryapitsyna'') by [[Andrei Konchalovsky]]\n* Soundtrack Stars Award\n**Critic's Choice Award: [[Alexandre Desplat]] (President of Venezia 71 Jury)\n**Best Soundtrack Award: ''Birdman'' by Alejandro Gonz\u00e1lez I\u00f1\u00e1rritu\n* Schermi di Qualit\u00e0 Award \u2013 Carlo Mazzacurati: ''Black Souls'' by Francesco Munzi\n* Human Rights Nights Award:\n**''On the Bride's Side'' by Antonio Augugliaro, Gabriele Del Grande, Khaled Soliman Al Nassiry\n**''The Look of Silence'' by Joshua Oppenheimer\n* Piccioni Award: soundtrack of ''Leopardi'' (music by [[Apparat (musician)|Sascha Ring]])\n* AssoMusica \u201cHo visto una Canzone\u201d Award: song ''Just One Day'', from the film ''Italy in a day''\n* \"Sorriso diverso Venezia 2014\" Award: ''On the Bride's Side'' by Antonio Augugliaro, Gabriele Del Grande, Khaled Soliman Al Nassiry\n* 1st Akai International Film Festival'''<ref name=Akai>{{cite web|url=http://nuovavenezia.gelocal.it/foto-e-video/2014/09/05/fotogalleria/venezia71-anime-nere-vince-il-premio-akai-migliori-attori-antonori-e-forte-1.9876659|title=Venezia71, Anime Nere vince il Premio Akai, migliori attori Antonori e Forte|date=5 September 2014|work=La Nuova di Venezia}}</ref>\n**Best Rivelation: Xin Yukun for  ''[[The Coffin in the Mountain]]''  \n**Best Direction: Francesco Munzi for ''Black Souls''\n**Best Actress: [[Iaia Forte]] for ''Leopardi'', ''The Show MAS Go On'' & ''La vita oscena''\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|2014 Venice Film Festival|71st Venice International Film Festival}}\n*{{official website|http://www.labiennale.org/en/cinema/}}\n*[https://www.imdb.com/event/ev0000681/2014/1/ Venice Film Festival 2014 Awards] on IMDb\n\n{{Venice Film Festival}}\n\n[[Category:Venice Film Festival]]\n[[Category:2014 film festivals|Venice Film Festival]]\n[[Category:2014 festivals in Europe|Venice Film Festival]]\n[[Category:2014 in Italian cinema|Venice Film Festival]]\n[[Category:2010s in Venice|Film]]\n[[Category:August 2014 events in Europe]]\n[[Category:September 2014 events in Europe]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Film festival}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2018}}\n{{Infobox Film festival\n|name = <small>71st Venice International Film Festival</small>\n|image = VeniceFilmFestival71poster.jpg\n|caption = Festival poster\n|opening = ''[[Birdman (film)|Birdman or (The Unexpected Virtue of Ignorance)]]''\n|closing = ''[[The Golden Era (film)|The Golden Era]]''\n|location = [[Venice]], Italy\n|founded = 1932\n|awards = [[Golden Lion]]: ''[[A Pigeon Sat on a Branch Reflecting on Existence]]''<br>[[Silver Lion]]: [[Andrei Konchalovsky]] (''[[The Postman's White Nights]]'')\n|host = [[Luisa Ranieri]]\n|number = \n|date = 27 August \u2013 6 September 2014\n|website = [http://www.labiennale.org/en/cinema/ Website]\n| chronology     = Venice Film Festival\n| preceded_by    = [[70th Venice International Film Festival|70th]]\n| followed_by    = [[72nd Venice International Film Festival|72nd]]\n}}\n\nThe '''71st annual [[Venice Film Festival|Venice International Film Festival]]''' took place in Venice, Italy between 27 August to 6 September 2014.<ref name=\"labiennale.org\">{{cite web|url=http://www.labiennale.org/en/cinema/71st-festival/line-up/ |title=71st Venice International Film Festival Line-Up |work=labiennale.org |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141007010534/http://www.labiennale.org/en/cinema/71st-festival/line-up/ |archivedate=7 October 2014 }}</ref> The festival opened with [[Alejandro Gonz\u00e1lez I\u00f1\u00e1rritu|Alejandro G. I\u00f1\u00e1rritu]]'s film ''[[Birdman (film)|Birdman]]'',<ref name=\"Birdman\">{{cite web |url=https://www.theguardian.com/film/2014/jul/10/birdman-venice-film-festival-opening-night |title=Birdman to hatch on opening night of Venice film festival|accessdate=10 July 2014 |work=The Guardian}}</ref><ref name=\"BirdmanBBC\">{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/entertainment-arts-28963398 |title=Venice Film Festival kicks off with Birdman |accessdate=28 August 2014 |work=BBC News}}</ref> and closed with [[Ann Hui]]'s drama film ''[[The Golden Era (film)|The Golden Era]]''.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://blogs.indiewire.com/womenandhollywood/ann-huis-the-golden-era-to-close-venice-film-festival |title=Ann Hui's The Golden Era to Close Venice Film Festival |accessdate=28 August 2014 |work=Indiewire |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140824164843/http://blogs.indiewire.com/womenandhollywood/ann-huis-the-golden-era-to-close-venice-film-festival |archive-date=24 August 2014 |url-status=dead }}</ref> Italian actress [[Luisa Ranieri]] hosted the opening and closing nights of the festival.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.labiennale.org/en/cinema/news/08-05.html?back=true |title=Luisa Ranieri to be the host of the 71st Venice Film Festival |accessdate=28 August 2014 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140714133638/http://labiennale.org/en/cinema/news/08-05.html?back=true |archivedate=14 July 2014 |url-status=dead  }}</ref> The Swedish film ''[[A Pigeon Sat on a Branch Reflecting on Existence]]'', directed by [[Roy Andersson]], won the [[Golden Lion]],<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/entertainment-arts-29098103 |title=Roy Andersson film scoops Venice Golden Lion award |accessdate=2 May 2018 |work=BBC News}}</ref> and [[Joshua Oppenheimer]]'s ''[[The Look of Silence]]'' won the [[Grand Jury Prize (Venice Film Festival)|Grand Jury Prize]].\n\nAmerican filmmakers [[Thelma Schoonmaker]] and [[Frederick Wiseman]] were the recipients of the Lifetime Achievement award.<ref name=\"Lifetime\">{{cite web |url=http://www.labiennale.org/en/cinema/news/18-07.html |title=Thelma Schoonmaker and Frederick Wiseman Golden Lions for Lifetime Achievement |accessdate=29 August 2014 |work=labiennale |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140903051855/http://www.labiennale.org/en/cinema/news/18-07.html |archive-date=3 September 2014 |url-status=dead  }}</ref> French composer [[Alexandre Desplat]] was the head of the jury for the main competition section.<ref name=\"Variety\"/>\n\nThe festival poster paid tribute to [[Fran\u00e7ois Truffaut]], as it featured the character of [[Antoine Doinel]] portrayed by [[Jean-Pierre L\u00e9aud]] from Truffaut's 1959 [[drama film]] ''[[The 400 Blows]]''.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/venice-film-fest-unveils-poster-716764 |title=Venice Film Fest Unveils Poster for 71st Edition|accessdate=28 August 2014 |work=The Hollywood Reporter}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.swide.com/art-culture/latest-venice-film-festival-2014-news-from-inarritus-birdman-to-classics-lineup/2014/07/22 |title=Venice Film Festival 2014: What we know so far|accessdate=28 August 2014 |work=Swide}}</ref>\n\n==Juries==\n'''Main Competition (Venezia 71)'''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.labiennale.org/en/cinema/71st-festival/juries/ |title=International Juries of the 71st Venice Film Festival |work=labiennale.org |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141007005126/http://www.labiennale.org/en/cinema/71st-festival/juries/ |archivedate=7 October 2014 }}</ref><ref name=\"Variety\">{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2014/film/news/french-film-composer-alexandre-desplat-to-head-venice-film-festival-jury-1201241763/|title=French Film Composer Alexandre Desplat To Head Venice Film Festival Jury|work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|date=23 June 2014|accessdate=23 June 2014}}</ref>\n*[[Alexandre Desplat]]: French composer (President of Jury)\n*[[Joan Chen]]: Chinese actress and director\n*[[Philip Groning]]: German director\n*[[Jessica Hausner]]: Austrian director\n*[[Jhumpa Lahiri]]: Indian novelist\n*[[Sandy Powell (costume designer)|Sandy Powell]]: English costume designer  \n*[[Tim Roth]]: British actor \n*[[Elia Suleiman]]: Palestinian director\n*[[Carlo Verdone]]: Italian actor and director\n\n'''Horizons (Orizzonti)'''<ref>{{cite web |url=https://variety.com/2014/film/news/venice-film-festival-reveals-lineup-for-its-71st-edition-1201268122/|title=Venice Film Festival Reveals Lineup for Its 71st Edition |accessdate=26 July 2014 |work=Variety}}</ref>\n*[[Ann Hui]]: Hong Kong director (President of Jury)\n*[[Moran Atias]]: Israeli actress\n*[[Pernilla August]]: Swedish actress and director\n*[[David Chase]]: American writer and director \n*[[Mahamat-Saleh Haroun]]: Chadian director \n* Roberto Minervini: Italian director\n* Alin Ta\u015f\u00e7\u0131yan: Turkish critic\n\n'''Opera Prima''' (Venice Award for a Debut Film)<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.labiennale.org/en/cinema/news/16-06.html|title=Alice Rohrwacher President of the International Jury for the Venice Award for a Debut Film |work=labiennale.org |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140903051851/http://www.labiennale.org/en/cinema/news/16-06.html |archivedate=3 September 2014 }}</ref>\n*[[Alice Rohrwacher]]: Italian director (President of Jury)\n*[[Lisandro Alonso]]: Argentine director\n*[[Ron Mann]]: Canadian filmmaker\n*[[Vivian Qu]]: Chinese filmmaker\n*[[Razvan Radulescu]]: Romanian novelist and film director\n\n==Official selection==\n\n===In Competition===\nThe following films were selected for the main competition:<ref name=\"InComp\">{{cite web|url