ete'' (\u041d\u0438\u0447\u0438\u0458\u0435 \u0434\u0435\u0442\u0435) || data-sort-value=\"Rsumovic\"| ''Vuk R\u0161umovi\u0107'' || Serbia\n|-\n| colspan=2| ''Villa Touma'' || data-sort-value=\"Arraf\"| Suha Arraf || Israel, Germany<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.cultframe.com/2014/08/villa-touma-film-suha-arraf/ |title= Villa Touma. Un film di Suha Arraf. 71\u00b0 Mostra Internazionale d\u2019Arte Cinematografica di Venezia. Settimana Internazionale della critica |language=French |accessdate=11 April 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.cineuropa.org/nw.aspx?t=newsdetail&l=en&did=261706 |title= Films from Israel at the Venice Film Festival: The Farewell Party and Vila Touma |accessdate=11 April 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.haaretz.com/life/movies-television/.premium-1.612768 |title= A guide for the perplexed: What\u2019s the story with 'Villa Touma\u2019? |accessdate=11 April 2018}}</ref>\n|}\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:95%; margin-top:2px\"\n! colspan=6| Special Events - Out of competition\n|-\n! Line-up\n! English title\n! Original title\n! Director(s)\n! Production country\n|-\n| Opening Film || colspan=2| ''Melbourne'' || Nima Javidi || Iran\n|-\n| Closing Film || ''The Market'' || ''Arance e Martello'' || Diego Bianchi || Italy\n|}\n\n===Venice Days===\nThe following films were selected for the 11th edition of the ''Venice Days (Giornate degli Autori)'' section:<ref name=\"Venice Days\">{{cite web |url=http://www.venice-days.com/2014/film.asp |title=Giornate degli Autori - Venice Days |accessdate=13 April 2018 |work=Giornate degli Autori}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"sortable wikitable\" style=\"width:95%; margin-bottom:0px\"\n! colspan=4| Official selection\n|-\n! English title\n! Original title\n! Director(s)\n! Production country\n|-\n| colspan=2| ''[[Before I Disappear]]'' || data-sort-value=\"Christensen\"| [[Shawn Christensen]] || United States\n|-\n| ''Between 10 and 12'' || ''Tussen 10 en 12'' || data-sort-value=\"Hoogendoorn\"