Large Logo.\n|-\n|align=center|'''D6975'''\n|align=center|37275\n|align=center|-\n|(Stainless Pioneer/Oor Wullie)\n|\n|[[Dartmouth Steam Railway]]\n|Operational. BR Blue\n|-\n|align=center|D6994\n|align=center|'''37294'''\n|align=center|-\n|\n|\n|Embsay\n|BR Blue\n|}\n\n== Model railways ==\nIn 1965 [[Hornby Railways]] launched its first version of the BR Class 37 in [[OO gauge]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hornbyguide.com/class_details.asp?classid=17|title=Hornby - BR Class 37 (Type 3) 1965|work=Hornby Railways Collector Guide|accessdate=31 January 2020}}</ref>\n\n== See also ==\n* [[Passenger locomotives in use in the UK]]\n* [[BR Class 37 renumbering]]\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist|colwidth=30em}}\n\n===Preserved locomotives===\n{{Reflist|group=pre|colwidth=30em}}\n\n== Sources ==\n* {{cite book |last=Clough |first=David N. |title=British Rail Standard Diesels of the 1960s |date=August 2009 |publisher=Ian Allan |location=Hersham |isbn=978-0-7110-3373-3 |id=0908/B1 |ref=harv }}\n* {{cite book |last=Earnshaw |first=Alan |title=Trains in Trouble: Vol. 8 |year=1993 |publisher=Atlantic Books |location=Penryn |isbn=0-906899-52-4 |ref=harv }}\n* {{cite book | last = Marsden | first = Colin J. | title = Motive power recognition:1 Locomotives | publisher = Ian Allan Ltd | year=  1981 | location = Shepperton | isbn = 0-7110-1109-5}}\n* {{cite book | last = Preedy | first = Norman E | last2 = Ford | first2 = H L | title = BR Diesels in Close-Up | publisher = D Bradford Barton Ltd | location = Truro}}\n* {{cite book | last = Williams | first = Alan | last2 = Percival | first2 = David | title = British Railways Locomotives and Multiple Units including Preserved Locomotives 1977 | publisher = Ian Allan Ltd | year=  1977 | location = Shepperton | isbn = 0-7110-0751-9}}\n\n==Further reading==\n* {{cite book|title=Locomotive Recognition: Class 37s|first1=David N.|last1=Clough|first2=D.I.|last2=Rapson|publisher=Ian Allan|year=1991|isbn=9780711019195|oclc=26632324}}\n* {{cite b