. Dutch undercoat\n|-\n|align=center|D6809\n|align=center|'''37109'''\n|align=center|-\n|\n|Privately owned, donated by [[DB Cargo UK|EWS]].\n|[[East Lancashire Railway]]\n|BR Blue\n|-\n|align=center|D6823\n|align=center|37123\n|align=center|'''37679'''\n|\n|Privately owned\n|Burton Wagon Works - Nemesis\n|Currently undergoing long-term restoration. Railfreight 3 Tone Grey: Unspecified Sub-Sector\n|-\n|align=center|D6842\n|align=center|'''37142'''\n|align=center|-\n|\n|\n|[[Bodmin & Wenford Railway]]<ref group=\"pre\">[http://www.bodminandwenfordrailway.co.uk/diesels/37142.html 37142] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080705093423/http://www.bodminandwenfordrailway.co.uk/diesels/37142.html |date=5 July 2008 }} ''bodminandwenfordrailway.co.uk''</ref>\n|\n|-\n|align=center|D6852\n|align=center|37152\n|align=center|'''37310'''\n|(British Steel Ravenscraig)\n|Privately owned<ref group=\"pre\" name=\"pr2\">[http://peakraildiesels.page.tl/37152.htm 37152] ''peakraildiesels''</ref>\n|[[Peak Rail]]<ref group=\"pre\" name=\"pr2\"/>\n|Large Logo Blue, in working order (Sept. 2006)<ref group=\"pre\" name=\"pr2\"/>\n|-\n|align=center|D6869\n|align=center|37169\n|align=center|'''37674'''\n|St Blaize Church 1445\u20131995\n|Privately owned\n|[[Wensleydale Railway|Stainmore Railway, Kirkby Stephen]]\n|Railfreight Red Stripe, operational (as of November 2014)\n|-\n|align=center|D6905\n|align=center|37205\n|align=center|'''37688'''\n|Great Rocks.\n|DO5 Ltd \n|[[Locomotive Services Limited]]\n|BR railfreight construction \n|-\n|align=center|D6915\n|align=center|'''37215'''\n|align=center|-\n|\n|The Growler Group [http://www.thegrowlergroup.org.uk/]\n|[[Gloucestershire Warwickshire Railway]]<ref name=\"gwr215\" group=\"pre\">[http://www.gwsr.com/html/locomotives.html Gloucester Warwickshire Railway - Locomotives (subsection 'diesel')] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090327200309/http://www.gwsr.com/html/locomotives.html |date=27 March 2009 }} ''gwsr.com''